originalText.text:
Who do I talk to because we were overpriced? $110 for overnight parking? And I was yelled at when I tried to explain we were quoted a different price. Do not park here.

Edit: This is incorrect. We may have been a little late, but certainly not 11 hours late. I know this because we arrived at our hotel in the afternoon, and we left approximately the same time the next day. I would have explained this, but we were being yelled at, and it was easier to take the loss. It’s water under the bridge, but do better in the future.

originalText.text: Very rude people working there, I got a reservation through Groupon and I checked I could park my SUV, when I got there, there was a guy who came out very rude saying that my car was too big and it was going to damage his elevator, kept saying to back out and kept leaving me talking by myself. I would not recommend anyone to go here, had to find parking somewhere else, it was less expensive but was late to our show.

originalText.text: Rudest people I’ve ever met.  DO NOT PARK HERE!  When we asked to move our car out of the way to change our 3 babies (All under two) quickly before our 2 hour ride home the guy blatantly told us “No, you can change them on the streets.”  Not to mention that there were other comments made from these people. There was plenty of room to move the car back to be out of the way.   Needless to say they will be getting a complaint tomorrow as well as a report to the BBB!

originalText.text: On 6 May, I reserved a parking spot from 7:45pm to 11:00pm. Arrived at 8:05 and the garage doors were closed and the attendant turned me away, saying that they were closed. When I told him I pre-payed/reserved, he said it wasn't his problem and walked off. If youre going to see The Book of Mormon, park at the place right next door instead of this place across the street.
